cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques to filter and analyze Twitter data for tracking influenza-like illnesses. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper deals with analyzing social media data, cs.SD (Sound) as the paper mentions emoticons, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with filtering and analyzing large amounts of data, and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper discusses the potential societal impact of using Twitter data for tracking illnesses.
